WEBVTT

00:00.546 --> 00:03.050
Hi, I'm Pastor Torin Brooks, and welcome to Faith Christian Church.

00:03.070 --> 00:04.532
So glad you decided to join us today.

00:05.113 --> 00:09.259
For the next 30 minutes, we'll be looking through God's Word and finding ways for it to apply to our lives today.

00:09.780 --> 00:11.262
I hope you enjoy it this morning, sermon.

00:11.963 --> 00:17.392
How many of you know that in the Bible, there are certain things that Jesus says, not if you do, but when you do?

00:19.495 --> 00:26.866
There are certain things that we as believers in Jesus Christ are, to some degree, almost, I would say required to do.

00:27.490 --> 00:43.874
And it's not because Jesus is trying to be mean and heat bomb more than we can handle, but what he's trying to do is sit inside of us a pattern of faithful living to where he can say, if you want to be like me and you want to, for people to see me in you, then you need to act like me.

00:44.275 --> 00:45.938
You need to be able to do the things I did.

00:46.859 --> 00:54.290
There were three things that Jesus said from the Sermon on the mountain, Matthew chapter six that were, that were not ifs, but wins.

00:55.650 --> 01:05.144
And I want to talk about one of those today because I believe sometimes in our lives, we mess up sometimes this definition of the word.

01:05.164 --> 01:13.036
And I want to be real clear about it today and maybe take it not a step farther than what it's supposed to be, but take it a step deeper in our own lives.

01:13.316 --> 01:14.458
And maybe we can gain from that.

01:14.518 --> 01:22.610
By the way, the three things Jesus said when we are to do them is give, pray, and fast.

01:25.186 --> 01:26.608
And I want to talk about fasting this morning.

01:27.909 --> 01:29.631
Let's give a clear definition of fasting.

01:30.031 --> 01:36.438
So if you, if you have your Bibles, you can open on the Matthew chapter six and we're going to start in verse number 16.

01:36.458 --> 01:50.654
This is what says, moreover, when you fast, do not be like the hypocrites with a sad countenance for they disfigure their faces that it may appear to men to be fasting.

01:51.355 --> 01:54.418
Surely I say to you, they have their reward.

01:54.978 --> 02:11.013
But you, when you fast, anoint your head and wash your face so that you do not appear to men to be fasting, but to your father who is in the secret place and your father who sees in secret will reward you openly.

02:11.794 --> 02:24.946
Verse 19, do not lay up for yourself treasures on earth where moth and rust destroy and where thieves break in and steal, but lay up for yourself treasures in heaven where neither moth nor rust destroys

02:25.058 --> 02:27.021
and where thieves do not break in and steal.

02:27.662 --> 02:32.288
For where your treasure is, there your heart will be also.

02:36.073 --> 02:37.495
Let's talk about fasting for a minute.

02:38.496 --> 02:46.007
In the beginning of time, when we start studying through, and we're not to this in our Exodus study yet, but when you study Exodus, you'll find that fasting is a part of the law.

02:46.708 --> 02:51.474
Every year, there were the Jewish people, when it came time to celebrate the day of Atonement,

02:51.650 --> 02:56.315
for around that period of time, there was a time that they were supposed to fast from something.

02:56.756 --> 03:01.681
Now, it seemed like a minor thing to do, but because it was something so simple.

03:02.302 --> 03:12.253
In fact, the Bible said the thing they were supposed to fast from, or to keep themselves from, was a little thing we formally call today, yeast, but back then in the Bible it was called leaven.

03:12.873 --> 03:20.722
Leaven was this symbol of, well, leaven was yeast, it was used in bread, obviously, to make the bread rise

03:20.866 --> 03:28.694
And before the children of Israel left the land of Egypt and went to the promised land, they were forced to rush out in the middle of the night.

03:29.155 --> 03:32.378
And they didn't have time to let bread rise, which I think is a shame.

03:35.422 --> 03:36.743
I like big thick bread.

03:37.264 --> 03:37.864
It's good.

03:38.385 --> 03:38.825
It's good.

03:38.966 --> 03:39.306
It's really good.

03:39.326 --> 03:46.834
But they were, they had these flat cakes and they had to make them fast because they knew they were going to have to get out of town quick.

03:47.138 --> 03:59.696
Now, you would think they weren't going to have to get out of town quick because what happened was after the first born of Egypt died, the Bible says that as they were leaving, they took the gold and the silver from Egypt with them and they all kind of walked out together.

04:00.197 --> 04:07.287
But how many of you know that Pharaoh, even though he was hard-hearted, wasn't dumb and blind and he said, oh, what did I do?

04:07.327 --> 04:08.228
I just let them go.

04:08.248 --> 04:09.109
I'm going to go get them back.

04:09.810 --> 04:15.378
So by God forcing them to leave quicker out of the land of Egypt, they got a head start down to the Red Sea.

04:15.778 --> 04:17.300
And we all know how that story ended.

04:18.121 --> 04:20.265
They finally made it across, took them a few years.

04:23.449 --> 04:25.092
Come on, that's true, took them a few years.

04:26.113 --> 04:30.820
And only two of them actually made it to the Promised Land from the very beginning trip, Joshua and Caleb.

04:31.882 --> 04:33.304
But in the end they got there in.

04:34.405 --> 04:43.158
So in the process of the feast, the idea was for the whole seven days they were not to have this leaven or this yeast.

04:43.939 --> 04:45.682
And part of it was the fact that

04:46.018 --> 04:50.424
This 11 was a symbol to the people of sin.

04:51.586 --> 04:53.829
And by sin, let's be real clear.

04:54.230 --> 05:00.899
It wasn't like they had a list from the mountain with the law of God of things they were to do and were not to do.

05:00.960 --> 05:05.787
Can I tell you, it's very, very simple when God makes a list for you.

05:06.988 --> 05:08.891
Some people say, well, what about this?

05:08.951 --> 05:09.632
What about that?

05:09.752 --> 05:11.455
How does this fall in?

05:11.515 --> 05:13.778
Well, look in the Bible and see.

05:14.498 --> 05:19.684
Sometimes God put a list in there for our benefit so we can know what things to avoid in our lives.

05:20.345 --> 05:29.515
And he said to leave the slaven out because it represents missing the market, represents falling short, and you're to leave it out and to stay away from it.

05:31.217 --> 05:42.130
And so as time went on, fasting became one of these things where people who wanted to have a closer relationship with God would fast, and to some degrees,

05:42.274 --> 05:49.483
Uh, there are different types of fasting, but some degrees not eat, not just things with leaven, but not eat at all.

05:49.924 --> 05:54.550
In order to show God how hungry they were to follow after him.

05:55.451 --> 06:02.581
In other words, it's the same thing when Jesus is in the wilderness and he says that wonderful scripture from Deuteronomy that man shall not live by what?

06:03.662 --> 06:04.243
Bread alone.

06:04.543 --> 06:06.706
So listen, there are more important things than food.

06:07.362 --> 06:11.287
And now some of us, you look at us and you wouldn't believe that, but it's true.

06:11.548 --> 06:13.450
There's some things that are more important than food.

06:14.151 --> 06:17.176
And throughout time, you would have people who would do fast.

06:17.236 --> 06:21.762
There was 21 day fast or 40 day fast, 10 day fast, seven day fast.

06:22.162 --> 06:35.040
But the idea was is that in order to show the show God that you were serious about following Him, you would leave things alone, primarily food, but leave things alone in order to focus on Him.

06:35.100 --> 06:36.402
Now it didn't work this way.

06:36.578 --> 06:41.663
because a lot of people when they think about fasting, this is how a normal fast goes in the average American household.

06:42.924 --> 06:49.010
Breakfast starts on the morning and they fix breakfast for everybody else and they say, well, I'm going to fast and I'm going to pray through breakfast.

06:49.030 --> 06:49.551
Well, that's good.

06:49.591 --> 06:50.552
That's what it's supposed to do.

06:50.572 --> 06:56.217
You're supposed to honor God with that time, but then what ends up happening is about 10 a.m.

07:01.202 --> 07:05.106
Some of you have never done this, but some of you, I see you look in some of your eyes and you're saying,

07:05.314 --> 07:07.298
Oh, he's talking about me.

07:07.318 --> 07:10.844
And all of a sudden the cheese hits on the kitchen counter look really good.

07:11.586 --> 07:15.132
And you say to yourself, self, I did really good fasting through breakfast.

07:15.172 --> 07:19.721
But you know, I don't think God would mind if I had a snack because I'm going to fast through lunch.

07:21.484 --> 07:26.834
But the idea of fasting was that it was a complete and total

07:27.362 --> 07:53.874
Climbing total fast it was something that was dedicated to God and by the way people who would fast in the Old Testament wouldn't go to work during their fast either They would fast and they would they would do consecrate themselves to God now by the time we see Jesus time Jesus does his own fasting as well the Bible talks in Matthew about him going out to the wilderness and he starts to fast and

07:54.018 --> 07:57.362
And he fasts for 40 days and 40 nights and the Bible says without food or water.

07:57.402 --> 07:59.344
I don't know if you realize it or not, but that's a miracle.

08:00.906 --> 08:04.491
Any person in a health profession will tell you that a person can live without food.

08:05.051 --> 08:15.985
Most people, not diabetics and not people with certain eating issues, but most people can live to some degree for 40 days without food.

08:16.485 --> 08:17.246
It has been done.

08:18.167 --> 08:23.634
I wouldn't recommend it unless God tells you to do it, but it's been done and people can't survive that.

08:23.842 --> 08:30.272
But most people will tell you, man cannot survive at the not too long without water.

08:30.953 --> 08:37.263
The average person, if they went without three days from water, would die of dehydration.

08:37.884 --> 08:45.896
And there are some people who can last up to seven days, those of us who have more water in our bodies than others, can last a few more days.

08:45.956 --> 08:52.306
But the idea is that after a while, the body would begin to dehydrate and you would die.

08:52.610 --> 09:01.580
Jesus is out in the wilderness and the Bible says he didn't drink or eat for 40 days and 40 nights and he comes out of this and is ministered to by the angels.

09:01.620 --> 09:10.890
But the idea was this was a miracle that he was able to do this and totally consecrating himself before he started his real earthly ministry by fasting.

09:11.791 --> 09:18.878
When it comes down to the mountain time though, Jesus is seeing two different styles of fasting.

09:19.840 --> 09:22.162
One is the style of the Pharisees.

09:22.242 --> 09:25.206
Now you've got to understand the Pharisees are not bad people.

09:26.088 --> 09:28.211
They're just people that don't understand it all.

09:28.751 --> 09:37.464
They're Pharisees were people that devoted their entire life to holiness, and they divided themselves, separated themselves to say, we're more holy than everyone else.

09:37.484 --> 09:42.111
We live to a higher standard, and what they would do is when they would fast, everybody knew it.

09:43.212 --> 09:50.002
Now, some people may be fasting that you know, and they let everybody know it because they're, oh, I can't go with you this week, brother.

09:50.498 --> 09:55.304
Oh, I'm just, I'm suffering for Jesus.

09:55.364 --> 09:56.885
You probably don't know anybody like that, do you?

09:58.307 --> 09:59.228
Don't look at the other person.

10:00.369 --> 10:04.334
But you had this idea that these Pharisees would do the same thing.

10:04.354 --> 10:07.217
They wanted everybody to know they were suffering for Jesus.

10:07.257 --> 10:10.761
And people pat him on the hand saying, oh, you're such a good Pharisee.

10:10.782 --> 10:11.743
You're doing so good.

10:11.763 --> 10:13.805
We're so proud of you for giving up for Jesus.

10:16.088 --> 10:18.130
We're gonna give you a sucker when this is all over.

10:19.490 --> 10:22.194
And they would, they would just be so proud of them.

10:22.234 --> 10:28.963
And Jesus comes on the scene and he sees this and he says, listen, this isn't the way fasting is supposed to go.

10:30.325 --> 10:38.717
Fasting was intended for your attention to be focused on Jesus, not for you to get attention from other people.

10:38.737 --> 10:40.599
I laughed, it wasn't too long ago.

10:40.720 --> 10:48.210
I was watching a website of a friend of mine's church and they had a fasting blog, fasting video blog,

10:48.482 --> 10:51.427
on the web so everyone can watch them go through a fast.

10:52.609 --> 11:02.084
And I, I, I simply called him up and I said, Tim, I said, I don't mean to be mean, but, but have you ever read Matthew chapter six?

11:03.747 --> 11:05.069
He replied, of course I have.

11:05.690 --> 11:07.153
I've been in ministry for 20 years.

11:08.154 --> 11:15.346
Did you, did you read the part in verse 16 about fasting in the open?

11:18.082 --> 11:22.287
He emailed me back later and said, yeah.

11:24.690 --> 11:26.472
I said, can we just be honest for a minute?

11:27.033 --> 11:33.120
Listen, part of the problem with living a Christian life is there's so many people doing it poorly.

11:35.363 --> 11:44.193
That's why Jesus says it's the hypocrites that are causing the problems because they say we want attention to go to God and yet the attention all comes to themselves.

11:44.534 --> 11:47.137
That was never the way God intended it to be.

11:47.157 --> 11:48.018
Do you understand that?

11:48.482 --> 11:50.105
It's never the way God intended it to be.

11:50.806 --> 11:56.897
Jesus says, listen, you've got to learn fasting is more than just not eating a meal.

11:56.997 --> 12:00.723
Fasting is giving of yourself for Jesus sake.

12:01.705 --> 12:11.602
It's giving of yourself, giving something up for him, giving something up so that he can be glorified and he can be exalted and you can be humble.

12:13.090 --> 12:25.264
I don't think sometimes we understand that the very definition of how we're supposed to live is so eloquently put by John the Baptist when he said about Jesus, he must increase and I must decrease.

12:26.285 --> 12:33.974
What fasting does is it takes all the attention off of, off of you, what's important to you and gets you back focused on what's important to God.

12:35.035 --> 12:37.458
Jesus said, listen, if you're going to fast,

12:37.570 --> 12:38.551
Do me a favor.

12:39.672 --> 12:43.236
That's a torn translation, but I think it fits well in the character of Jesus.

12:43.616 --> 12:47.740
It says, listen, if you're going to fast, do me a favor.

12:48.100 --> 12:51.984
He says, when you fast, anoint your head.

12:56.048 --> 12:56.849
What does that mean?

12:58.370 --> 12:59.571
I thought long and hard about that.

12:59.592 --> 13:01.353
Why anoint your head?

13:01.894 --> 13:02.755
Do you smell bad?

13:03.335 --> 13:06.258
Because anointing was a perfume type of thing.

13:06.370 --> 13:09.075
When people did it right, you could smell it for half a mile away.

13:09.115 --> 13:10.197
If the wind was blowing, right?

13:11.138 --> 13:13.803
You know, I think it was, in fact, I think it was very interesting.

13:13.823 --> 13:14.844
I'll throw this in for side note.

13:14.865 --> 13:26.805
It won't cost you anything, but I throw this in for side note that Jesus feet were anointed right before he went to the cross and the anointing oil she used on the feet of Jesus would have still been smelled by the soldiers at these feet.

13:29.189 --> 13:29.810
Interesting in it.

13:32.610 --> 13:35.494
I mean, the thing is, is that he says, listen, anoint your head.

13:35.534 --> 13:37.417
What do you think he means by an anoint your head?

13:37.437 --> 13:38.599
Well, I'll tell you what I think he means.

13:38.940 --> 13:43.887
I think he means stand up straight and be standing who you are.

13:47.292 --> 13:49.415
Cover up under his anointing.

13:50.076 --> 13:54.924
The anointing was something that was supposed to be symbolized as a follower of God.

13:54.984 --> 13:58.549
The priests were anointed, Kings were anointed, but he says anoint your head.

13:58.569 --> 13:59.250
He says, listen,

13:59.938 --> 14:03.523
Uh, cover up this fact that you're suffering for yourself and wash your face.

14:04.404 --> 14:04.744
I love that.

14:04.784 --> 14:07.408
Wash your face part.

14:07.688 --> 14:09.170
Don't, don't look so pitiful.

14:10.532 --> 14:11.733
Don't look so sad.

14:12.755 --> 14:14.116
I know some of you miss food.

14:15.278 --> 14:18.642
I know some of you like pecan pie, but don't worry.

14:18.702 --> 14:20.404
That's not what it's for.

14:21.646 --> 14:27.794
He says, listen, you're going to have to be willing to give up and then act like you're not giving up anything.

14:30.146 --> 14:31.167
I think that's the hard part.

14:31.187 --> 14:34.530
Sometimes when we give up something, we want everybody in the world to know it.

14:36.092 --> 14:39.855
I know people who used to...

14:39.875 --> 14:40.836
Boy, I better not say this.

14:45.080 --> 14:46.482
Let me get behind the bulletproof glass.

14:47.643 --> 14:51.747
I used to know people who would say, hey, you'll never guess what we did.

14:52.107 --> 14:56.351
We gave this amount of money to charity this week.

14:56.371 --> 14:56.671
Great.

14:57.272 --> 14:58.873
Love that.

14:58.893 --> 14:59.634
I don't even know.

15:01.730 --> 15:03.352
I had a friend of mine in Memphis one time.

15:03.752 --> 15:04.653
He was so proud.

15:04.894 --> 15:07.537
Gave $10,000 to St. Jude.

15:07.897 --> 15:11.141
He said, man, he goes, man, what do you think about that?

15:12.022 --> 15:14.224
I said, I think you got what you deserve.

15:16.547 --> 15:20.251
See, the Bible says that when we boast in ourselves, we get our reward.

15:20.831 --> 15:24.876
Jesus said, if you want a real reward, lay up for yourself treasures in heaven.

15:24.896 --> 15:26.738
See, that's why I read that next verse last.

15:27.394 --> 15:33.881
Because when we give up stuff just so we can get attention, then we're not going to get what we really should be getting out of fasting.

15:35.923 --> 15:37.425
What we get is human applause.

15:37.465 --> 15:38.326
And let me tell you something.

15:38.606 --> 15:42.551
Human applause and human favor last for about six milliseconds.

15:45.754 --> 15:47.115
Well, Pastor, how do you figure that out?

15:47.956 --> 15:49.078
Just watch the Oscars.

15:51.100 --> 15:56.786
These people cheer for a Hollywood actor one week and he puts out a bad film and they hate him the rest of his life.

15:58.754 --> 16:04.502
Look, human favor and human applause last for either as long as the person is alive or as long as you're their friend.

16:04.842 --> 16:06.705
And as soon as you mess up, it's over with.

16:07.025 --> 16:08.267
And what's the purpose of that?

16:10.370 --> 16:16.478
He says, you want real treasure, you want real, you want what you do to last for eternity, do it for the Lord.

16:17.379 --> 16:18.501
You don't do it for anybody else.

16:20.924 --> 16:26.211
Well, pastor, you know, but what about what about what I'm doing?

16:26.231 --> 16:27.413
What about what I'm giving up?

16:27.473 --> 16:28.434
Doesn't that count?

16:29.890 --> 16:32.273
Well, yeah, if you do it in the right attitude, in the right spirit.

16:33.374 --> 16:36.097
But that's why Jesus called the people that did it wrong, hypocrites.

16:36.578 --> 16:42.304
He said, listen, he goes, do not appear to men to be fasting, but to your father who is in the secret place.

16:44.327 --> 16:46.489
And the father is in secret or reward you openly.

16:49.713 --> 16:52.997
He said, listen, if you're going to give it up, give it up for the right reason.

16:53.838 --> 16:55.800
If you're going to give up food, give it up for the right reason.

16:55.820 --> 16:57.362
If you're going to give up something else,

16:58.914 --> 17:02.299
Sometimes people tell me, well, pastor, I can't give up food because I have to eat.

17:03.381 --> 17:05.244
And I said, well, what are you willing to give up?

17:07.327 --> 17:09.070
Can I just talk about that for a few more minutes?

17:11.514 --> 17:13.036
There are a whole bunch of stories in you.

17:13.336 --> 17:16.622
We always pick on Jesus for picking 12 disciples.

17:17.803 --> 17:19.606
If you're up to me, I'd have left out eight of them.

17:19.646 --> 17:20.568
I'd have just picked four.

17:22.391 --> 17:24.594
There were only really four that never gave him any trouble.

17:25.442 --> 17:30.050
You know, I left out Peter because Peter just, yeah, all the time.

17:30.631 --> 17:34.478
I left out Jews to scare it because, you know, backstabber.

17:34.498 --> 17:39.227
And I left out a couple others, but I kept Andrew because, you know, he brings me food.

17:41.310 --> 17:44.717
I picked Judas because he didn't give us any problem.

17:46.219 --> 17:47.762
Bartholomew.

17:47.842 --> 17:48.803
Thomas, he's gone.

17:49.264 --> 17:52.207
But you know, you have all these, you pick and choose, but Jesus said he picked 12.

17:52.488 --> 17:57.514
And in fact, if we're really honest with ourselves and count all the people that Jesus called to follow him, there was more.

17:59.937 --> 18:00.517
There was more.

18:03.761 --> 18:05.583
And in that moment, can you imagine this?

18:05.744 --> 18:15.275
Jesus, the person who they think is the Messiah, the chosen Savior, come to free them from the Romans, which by the way, wasn't a bad idea.

18:16.617 --> 18:17.618
Free them from the Romans.

18:18.306 --> 18:19.988
and to restore the national Israel.

18:20.930 --> 18:23.213
Here's a guy who they've been waiting for all their lives.

18:23.934 --> 18:26.778
And he comes up and says, you can follow me if you.

18:30.604 --> 18:33.849
I remember the one guy, very famous story, of course.

18:35.070 --> 18:39.036
One guy comes to Jesus and he goes, hey, what do I gotta do to sign up?

18:40.238 --> 18:41.399
Jesus said, what have you been doing?

18:41.420 --> 18:42.581
He goes, I've been following the law.

18:42.601 --> 18:43.202
He goes, great.

18:43.663 --> 18:44.744
Of course, now he lists the law.

18:44.764 --> 18:45.906
He lists the things that he did.

18:46.498 --> 18:48.240
You know, I don't, I honor my father, my mother.

18:48.260 --> 18:49.941
I haven't steeled or killed anybody today.

18:50.582 --> 18:52.464
You know, I haven't done this, haven't done that.

18:52.764 --> 18:53.585
Jesus goes, great.

18:53.625 --> 18:54.987
Now tell you what you need to do.

18:55.968 --> 18:59.551
What you need to do now is I want you to sell everything you have, give it to the poor and come follow me.

19:02.674 --> 19:10.883
Now obviously Jesus doesn't ask that of all of us, but I've never known a person that Jesus didn't ask something of us.

19:13.545 --> 19:14.226
Now listen to me.

19:15.394 --> 19:18.779
I've never met a person, Jesus asked them to give up everything of themselves.

19:19.921 --> 19:26.652
But I've never met a person, Jesus didn't ask them to give some of themselves, something of theirs, a way, something that theirs up.

19:28.635 --> 19:40.113
This man was so enamored with his identity being in his riches that the Bible doesn't call him by name, the Bible refers to him as a rich, young ruler.

19:42.617 --> 19:43.378
And he knew

19:43.650 --> 19:47.934
that if he gave away his riches, his identity would just be that guy.

19:49.836 --> 19:50.937
And he couldn't deal with that.

19:52.259 --> 19:57.404
With others, there was one guy who said he had to go say goodbye to his mother and father, he should have learned from Elisha.

19:58.405 --> 20:02.028
And you had this other man who had to go somewhere else and do business.

20:02.909 --> 20:11.538
All these people had the same problems, and then there's a whole crowd of people around Jesus one day, and he says this one thing, he goes, unless you deny yourself,

20:12.706 --> 20:14.188
Take up your cross and follow me.

20:14.228 --> 20:17.173
You can't be my disciple and people left.

20:19.156 --> 20:19.736
People left.

20:22.561 --> 20:24.163
You said, well, what's that got to do with fasting?

20:24.263 --> 20:27.989
Everything because to give up party yourself is just like fasting.

20:28.730 --> 20:34.258
You're surrendering a part of your life to Jesus or hopefully all of your life to Jesus.

20:34.882 --> 20:49.905
See, I think Jesus, as I follow his track, as he's teaching and ministering and working on his disciples, every time he was with them, he was molding them and creating something inside of them that he would use later once he was gone and sent his Holy Spirit.

20:50.466 --> 21:00.642
And everything he's doing with the disciples, he's changing them little by little and molding them here and chipping this off there and he's trying to help them learn to be.

21:00.702 --> 21:03.346
And all the time, he goes from this

21:03.810 --> 21:06.714
this idea of come and see to come and die.

21:06.754 --> 21:15.606
And at the end, he's asking them to surrender everything and the people who are around the disciples, some of them left.

21:15.626 --> 21:20.232
Because the idea of not being in charge of our own lives makes us furious.

21:21.554 --> 21:33.810
In fact, I would be willing to tell you today that of the majority of the people I meet, nor their new England, many of them don't mind Jesus telling them they need to show up to church.

21:34.338 --> 21:35.179
on Sunday morning.

21:36.600 --> 21:52.675
They don't even mind Jesus telling them to, uh, given the offering, but very few of them like the idea of being told they have to live for Jesus Christ every day of the week.

21:52.695 --> 21:53.696
24 hours a day.

21:56.339 --> 21:58.221
We used to call the process snoring for Jesus.

22:02.865 --> 22:03.826
What do you mean, pastor?

22:04.386 --> 22:09.192
I mean, giving of yourself completely to him.

22:10.694 --> 22:13.718
Well, pastor, I don't like that idea because I kind of like who I am.

22:14.019 --> 22:18.264
Well, I like all y'all too.

22:18.284 --> 22:25.874
But there are certain things though, and all of us that we need to surrender and give to him and give up.

22:25.894 --> 22:31.602
You know, when the, when the Bible is talking about fasting of foods for some of us, we ought to be fasting other things.

22:33.666 --> 22:34.727
and giving it to the Lord.

22:35.829 --> 22:38.092
Like I don't know, our time.

22:40.094 --> 22:52.290
You'd be surprised if you were to take a log of last week and write down how you spent every five minute period of every day, some of us would be surprised how little time God had in our lives.

22:55.134 --> 23:01.682
In fact, I think some of us, if we were to take, in fact, I would be willing to bet if you were to take that time log to Africa,

23:03.362 --> 23:10.871
and go over to one of these small tribes, they would believe that you don't worship God, you worship TV.

23:15.576 --> 23:17.758
Or this other longer word called computer.

23:21.863 --> 23:22.744
You know, it never fails.

23:23.145 --> 23:24.706
I shouldn't say this, but I am.

23:24.947 --> 23:31.314
You know, I sometimes, every time that I need to motivate myself to clean my house,

23:31.394 --> 23:33.196
I go watch that A&E show, Hoarders.

23:36.080 --> 23:37.982
And that just turns on my motivation.

23:38.002 --> 23:44.010
Because as soon as I see, I mean, five minutes into it, I'm picking up little micro pieces and stuff off the carpet.

23:44.030 --> 23:46.854
Because I'm like, boy, I'm not letting my house get that way.

23:47.875 --> 23:50.218
But you know what I always noticed in those houses?

23:50.819 --> 23:51.700
There are two things.

23:52.300 --> 23:55.204
If the power's on in that house, there are two things in every house.

23:55.885 --> 23:59.890
There's a clear space to the TV and a clear space to the computer.

24:01.122 --> 24:16.087
And the only times you don't see that is when the power's been shut off and when they show the opening scene of them living in somebody else's house, they're either in front of a computer or they're in front of a TV.

24:16.107 --> 24:27.026
I would be willing to bet that if we were to value our lives in time period increments, we would find out if really if our

24:27.138 --> 24:31.024
our treasure and our heart are together on things.

24:31.064 --> 24:36.812
We spend the most time with what we treasure the most.

24:36.832 --> 24:41.879
And it's awkward that we find ourselves surrounded by other things besides God.

24:43.321 --> 24:52.114
I said this Wednesday night, I really meant it, or maybe Sunday night, but listen, there was a time in the Bible where men and women used to walk with God.

24:53.346 --> 24:55.309
Remember Adam and Eve took time.

24:55.689 --> 24:58.694
And I don't know what they were too busy in the garden.

24:58.714 --> 25:01.378
They were probably doing things that needed to be taken here.

25:01.398 --> 25:03.381
The Bible said they were there to tend and keep the garden.

25:03.701 --> 25:10.291
But there were times when Adam and Eve actually took time out of their schedule to walk with God.

25:10.311 --> 25:11.393
They actually walked with him.

25:11.673 --> 25:12.775
They talked with him.

25:13.155 --> 25:14.818
I don't know what the conversations were.

25:16.019 --> 25:16.320
Hi.

25:17.121 --> 25:18.122
Hi.

25:18.143 --> 25:18.703
How you doing?

25:19.905 --> 25:21.928
Same old same old.

25:21.948 --> 25:23.250
It's a great day in the garden.

25:23.746 --> 25:25.968
The sunshine and do on the ground.

25:26.228 --> 25:26.789
It's nice.

25:27.610 --> 25:28.250
How are you doing?

25:29.111 --> 25:29.652
I'm doing?

25:30.693 --> 25:32.014
Hey, I don't know what they talked about.

25:32.034 --> 25:36.799
All I know is they took time to spend with each other, took time to do with each other.

25:37.119 --> 25:42.745
And today we look at our busy schedules and we go, we don't even know how we have time to walk on a treadmill or not.

25:43.485 --> 25:46.148
Let alone walk with God.

25:46.168 --> 25:52.274
I'm not a big fan of the treadmill anyway, but do we even have time to spend time with God?

25:52.354 --> 25:57.663
We even have priority that Jesus is Lord and Savior of our lives.

25:58.725 --> 26:05.997
I think the biggest problem that I have in my own life is thinking that the things of ministry are actually more important than my relationship with God.

26:08.081 --> 26:14.231
And sometimes getting so caught up in doing the actual physical work of ministry, forget that I need to spend time with God alone.

26:15.213 --> 26:18.418
I need to take time to walk daily with God, to spend

26:18.498 --> 26:25.129
Time, not just studying this word for what I'm gonna talk about tonight or Wednesday night, but actually taking time out and saying, you know what?

26:25.610 --> 26:26.992
I don't need as much TV.

26:30.498 --> 26:35.927
In fact, some of you would probably be a lot nicer people Wednesday if you fasted TV Tuesday night this week.

26:38.872 --> 26:39.934
Oh, come on, that was funny.

26:41.296 --> 26:43.880
So you're like, honey, what's on TV Tuesday night?

26:44.241 --> 26:45.042
The election!

26:48.322 --> 26:56.095
The elections on TV on Tuesday night, some of you are so frustrated with what's going on anyway, you're going to be mad no matter what the result is.

26:56.757 --> 26:59.621
You'd be much better off fasting TV Tuesday night.

26:59.641 --> 27:00.423
You'd be a lot happier.

27:00.483 --> 27:00.884
Everybody be.

27:01.224 --> 27:02.186
Why are you so happy?

27:02.206 --> 27:05.311
Well, I spent all night, last night with the Lord.

27:08.336 --> 27:09.178
You know what I've noticed?

27:09.338 --> 27:13.906
I have never had a bad time when I take time to spend with the Lord.

27:18.946 --> 27:21.909
I was about to say something to get me in deep trouble, but I won't do it.

27:23.310 --> 27:24.111
Yeah, I will.

27:25.773 --> 27:26.253
Yeah, I will.

27:27.394 --> 27:28.195
I'm gonna hide though.

27:29.756 --> 27:30.697
See, I've learned something.

27:33.040 --> 27:35.422
When you spend time with people, sometimes it's good time.

27:36.143 --> 27:37.224
Sometimes it's bad time.

27:38.765 --> 27:40.106
Sometimes you can have good dates.

27:41.628 --> 27:42.809
Sometimes you can have bad dates.

27:44.390 --> 27:45.512
But you know what I find interesting?

27:45.592 --> 27:48.114
I've never had a bad time with God.

27:48.418 --> 27:49.961
when I take time to spend with Him.

27:52.585 --> 27:56.853
I never leave the presence of God more frustrated than when I came in.

27:59.878 --> 28:03.925
I never find myself more angry at God when I leave.

28:04.646 --> 28:10.256
In fact, I may come in to the day talking with God saying, I can't believe you put me through this.

28:10.316 --> 28:14.002
And then all of a sudden I leave going, thank you Lord for allowing me to feel your presence.

28:17.986 --> 28:29.481
See, I think God put fasting into our mindset and into the scriptures and into the law and into the message Jesus had to remind us that this life is really not all about us.

28:32.965 --> 28:34.307
I'm glad nobody believes me.

28:34.928 --> 28:40.395
Now, listen, I'm telling you, He put fasting in to remind us this life is not all about us.

28:41.957 --> 28:43.118
This life is about Him.

28:43.178 --> 28:46.002
This world was created by Him.

28:46.338 --> 28:47.960
for his pleasure, for his benefit.

28:48.300 --> 28:53.867
And this whole line that we live is about serving him and loving him and him teaching us how to love each other.

28:55.810 --> 29:00.936
But if we don't get this relationship right with him, we're never going to get these relationships right.

29:02.718 --> 29:06.783
If this relationship is broken, all these relationships will never make sense.

29:08.986 --> 29:12.070
Because if you don't have love from God, you're not going to have love to love one another.

29:13.291 --> 29:15.474
The Bible says in 1 John that love is of God.

29:16.258 --> 29:18.481
And everyone that loves is born of God and knows God.

29:18.741 --> 29:22.987
If this is not working, these relationships will never work.

29:23.007 --> 29:25.230
And if we don't take time to say, you know what?

29:26.131 --> 29:28.394
My relationship with God is more important than food.

29:30.577 --> 29:33.120
Or my relationship with God is more important than TV.

29:35.384 --> 29:36.525
Even if it is a football game.

29:39.890 --> 29:41.331
Even though LSU lost.

29:41.532 --> 29:46.258
But anyway, even if it is a football game or your favorite TV show,

29:46.370 --> 29:47.131
whatever that may be.

29:48.794 --> 29:56.126
Or maybe, maybe you don't need to know everything there is to know about people on Facebook.

29:56.146 --> 29:56.366
Oh.

30:01.996 --> 30:03.077
Did I hit a hard note there?

30:03.117 --> 30:03.698
I'm sorry.

30:05.582 --> 30:05.902
Hello?

30:06.663 --> 30:07.364
Can we be honest?

30:07.865 --> 30:10.770
I mean, really, if we can't be honest in church, where we're going to be honest, right?

30:13.250 --> 30:15.893
I mean, my mind might as well not be the Facebook network.

30:15.913 --> 30:17.315
It might as well be the gossip network.

30:19.737 --> 30:26.525
I mean, people really uplift and support one another on Facebook.

30:27.947 --> 30:29.929
Or maybe I just have the wrong people on mine.

30:31.110 --> 30:35.315
But a lot of times I see stuff on Facebook and I'm thinking, wow, I don't need this.

30:36.136 --> 30:37.938
Or I didn't need to know this about that person.

30:39.874 --> 30:43.518
And then, you know, some people will get on and they'll play games or they'll be on.

30:43.899 --> 30:46.001
Pastor, stop picking on me about my computer.

30:46.342 --> 30:47.983
I'm talking to you about your life.

30:50.346 --> 30:53.670
God wants more from you than just a Sunday morning commitment.

30:56.493 --> 31:03.922
God wants more from you than just the appearance of I look like I'm doing what's right instead of you need to be doing what's right.

31:06.946 --> 31:08.968
Passing is more than just a requirement.

31:09.348 --> 31:17.316
It's a lifestyle privilege that we have to say, Lord, I'd love you enough to give up the things that I cherish in order to show you how much I love you.

31:20.439 --> 31:23.842
Some people have made the ultimate sacrifice in giving all.

31:24.923 --> 31:26.645
Do you know, there's a scripture in the Bible that says this.

31:27.926 --> 31:29.928
He tries to save his own life, we'll lose it.

31:32.850 --> 31:35.993
In other words, if you think all the things around you were important, guess what?

31:36.074 --> 31:36.594
They're not.

31:38.466 --> 31:41.170
Hey, listen, can I be honest with you this morning?

31:41.931 --> 31:42.892
I love my iPad.

31:43.793 --> 31:50.683
It's fun to play with, have games on it that my kids play that I'm better at, because I play longer.

31:50.703 --> 31:53.487
I shouldn't, but I do.

31:54.248 --> 31:54.829
But you know what?

31:54.969 --> 31:58.994
That iPad will one day go the route of every other electronic device we've ever owned.

32:00.156 --> 32:02.159
I hope it won't end up in the tub again.

32:02.539 --> 32:07.506
But the point is, is that they sank one, and it was great, you know?

32:07.618 --> 32:09.521
Who knew you couldn't play them in the bathtub?

32:11.724 --> 32:12.224
Kids didn't.

32:12.525 --> 32:15.950
But listen, all those things are going to be gone.

32:17.031 --> 32:17.632
Do you know what?

32:17.792 --> 32:19.635
One day this building we're in is going to be gone.

32:21.537 --> 32:24.902
If something doesn't happen to it, a hurricane doesn't knock it down.

32:25.823 --> 32:28.347
The ditch behind the church will claim it in 50 years.

32:29.949 --> 32:33.714
It's not the things.

32:35.266 --> 32:37.769
that matter, it's our relationship with God that matters.

32:39.511 --> 32:43.435
Everything we have can be taken away in a moment's notice.

32:43.675 --> 33:01.394
As I think about it in closing, I think about those people that lost everything during this last hurricane, how when they went to bed on Monday night, they may or may not have known where they stood, but when they woke up and saw things gone, or maybe they turned on the TV at the shelter and they were able to see that everything they worked their life for

33:01.506 --> 33:07.353
had gone away, it makes you realize that some things are worth giving up in order to make this connection with God strong.

33:10.576 --> 33:13.379
Because the Bible says he was willing to lose his life for my sake.

33:14.060 --> 33:14.601
We'll find it.

33:18.105 --> 33:29.778
And I'm going to encourage you, all of you who serve God and love Jesus, ask him today, what can I give up to serve you better?

33:31.010 --> 33:34.435
What can I surrender to you to show you how much I love you?

33:35.937 --> 33:42.026
And how can I learn to make giving up things a part of my daily life?

33:45.090 --> 33:48.475
Thank you for watching today's service, but you really should visit in person.

